How did you know that?

242
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:08,880
How did you know she had pink pearl earrings on?

243
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:12,680
You're really grasping for straws, aren't you?

244
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:15,580
Well, it's obvious that...

245
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,480
She told me

246
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,880
that she bought those tonight on the spur of the moment

247
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:31,480
just before meeting you here tonight.

248
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:36,980
Which means, you couldn't have seen them until you saw her here.

249
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:40,280
And in this spot with the lights down so low,

250
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:43,680
those pink pearls look like mere dark balls.

251
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:47,880
There's no way you could tell that it was pink.

252
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:51,980
That's right. Not unless...

253
00:14:51,980 --> 00:14:55,580
you opened this door of light

254
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:59,580
while you were kissing her.

255
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:05,580
Mr. Ooba, you couldn't have...

256
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:12,280
Mr. Ooba, why don't you answer me?

257
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:15,680
Tell us why you opened the door.

258
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,380
You're asking me why?

259
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:22,580
The answer is simple.

260
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,380
Because I made a promise to my father.

261
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:28,780
That I would avenge his death.

262
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:36,780
Avenge your father's death?

263
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:42,480
Yes. My father also had a rather big game company.

264
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,980
That was until 20 years ago

265
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:47,480
when her father suggested their companies merge.

266
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:52,480
He suggested they open an office in the Beika Center Building.

267
00:15:53,980 --> 00:15:57,680
But he wasn't planning a merger, he was planning a take over.

268
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:01,580
All the game creating know-how my father constructed was stolen

269
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:06,580
and all the employees in my father's company were laid off.

270
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:08,280
And my father...

271
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:10,480
who was vice president in name only,

272
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:12,980
was so full of despair, so he killed himself.

273
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:15,880
But papa took such good care of you.

274
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:20,180
Yes. I think it was because he felt guilty.

275
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:23,180
That's why he kept promoting me.

276
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:26,880
Me, the man who planned to kill him,

277
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:31,280
marry his daughter and take over the company.

278
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:33,380
No way...

279
00:16:33,380 --> 00:16:35,480
It was all a game.

280
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:38,880
The story line was the hero uses the powers of evil

281
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:42,480
to overthrow the demon.

282
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:46,480
But who would have thought it would end the same way.

283
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,680
What do you mean by that?

284
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:52,580
My father was murdered, but it was made to look like a suicide.

285
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:54,880
He was killed 20 years ago,

286
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:58,180
right here in this very building by Mr. Tatsumi.

287
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:01,180
But someone saw through the crime.

288
00:17:01,180 --> 00:17:02,780
It was a young man like you,

289
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:06,480
he figured it out just like you did tonight.

290
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,780
I guess when you borrow the powers of evil,

291
00:17:07,780 --> 00:17:10,180
you have to pay the price.

292
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:12,680
Yes, that's it! I remember it now!

293
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:14,680
It was Yusaku!

294
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:17,180
Yusaku Kudo butted in when we were investigating the case

295
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:20,780
and he solved it for us!

296
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:24,580
Oh, you're talking about that mystery writer.

297
00:17:24,580 --> 00:17:28,580
Which means the son solved the crime which arose

298
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:32,480
from the crime committed 20 years ago which the father solved.

299
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:35,480
Isn't that ironic? Don't you think, Kudo?

300
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,080
Kudo?

301
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:48,280
Please. I need a little more time.

302
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:51,180
She... she's waiting for me.

303
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:56,580
I can't turn into Conan again now.

304
00:18:00,980 --> 00:18:02,080
Haibara?

305
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,880
You...

306
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,380
why...

307
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:10,180
24 minutes over time.

308
00:18:10,180 --> 00:18:12,980
I guess that's the maximum tolerance level.

309
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:14,780
I'll consider this a loan.

310
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:19,980
Edogawa.

311
00:18:19,980 --> 00:18:23,880
Hey, did you hear? The murder's been solved.

312
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,380
Is that true?

313
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:27,680
You're finally going to get to see him, aren't you?

314
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,180
I mean, your boyfriend.

315
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:31,880
For goodness sakes. He is not my boyfriend.

316
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,980
Conan?

317
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:40,380
Here, take this card.

318
00:18:40,380 --> 00:18:43,380
Shinichi told me to give it to you.

319
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:46,380
Uncle Kogoro told me to come check up on you,

320
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:48,280
and I ran into Shinichi.

321
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,880
Is dad here, too?

322
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,880
Yes. He's waiting in the parking lot downstairs.

323
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,780
Gosh, what's taking that kid so long?

324
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:58,080
It's already been one hour!

325
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:00,380
I can't wait anymore, I'm going to go have a look myself.

326
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:02,080
No, I better just wait.

327
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,580
That wouldn't be adult of me.

328
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:06,180
Darn it.

329
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,680
So, where is Shinichi?

330
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,880
Well...

331
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:12,480
It's like this, he got a call on his cellular,

332
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,680
it was about a case he worked on recently

333
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:16,580
saying something terrible happened

334
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:19,480
and so he ran off.

335
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,780
I see.

336
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:25,080
Shinichi is stupid, isn't he?

337
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:28,980
Leaving you all alone like this.

338
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:31,080
So, he left me behind again.

339
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:37,680
You know,

340
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,280
Shinichi told me that...

341
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:41,280
No! Stop it!

342
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,780
I don't want to hear it!

343
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:46,580
I don't want to hear it.

344
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:48,080
No more excuses from him.

345
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:06,080
Shinichi told me...

346
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:11,080
that one day...

347
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:13,480
One day, for sure...

348
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,480
He'll come back even if it kills him.

349
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:20,580
That's why...

350
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,180
That's why...

351
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:32,180
He wants you to wait for him. That's what he said.

352
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:45,480
That's why...

353
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:49,280
You're so silly.

354
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:52,180
Conan, you don't have to put on such a serious face.

355
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:54,080
It's all that eager beaver detective's fault,

356
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:57,680
he drops everything and runs off at the mere mention of a case.

357
00:20:57,680 --> 00:21:00,880
Eager beaver detective?

358
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:03,580
Oh, I almost forgot! Conan, would you like some dessert?

359
00:21:03,580 --> 00:21:05,780
Yes, sure.

360
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:07,580
Excuse me, dessert menu please.

361
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:09,180
Here you go.

362
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,780
Good grief.

363
00:22:56,780 --> 00:22:59,880
He has some nerve, asking me to wait for him!

364
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:02,680
Who does he think I am, his mother?

365
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,480
That makes five desserts.

366
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:10,980
But I'd still like to know what he wanted to talk to me about.

367
00:23:10,980 --> 00:23:13,480
Conan, aren't you curious too?

368
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:16,480
Huh? No, not really.

369
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:18,980
Well, since he ran off without telling me,

370
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:22,480
I guess it wasn't very important.

371
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,780
I just don't understand

372
00:23:23,780 --> 00:23:26,980
why he picked such an expensive restaurant

373
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:28,680
What a fool.

374
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:31,080
Making such a big deal when he had nothing important to say.

375
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:36,080
I don't know how to tell her.

376
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:41,680
I picked this place for good luck...

377
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:49,980
since dad proposed to mom here.

378
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,380
What's taking so long?

379
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,100
Next Conan's Hint:

380
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,900
"Haru-yo-koi"

